article.headline: Ohio 74, William &amp, Mary 55
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Jerome Tillman scored 19 points, including 11 in the second half to help Ohio pull away from William and Mary for a 74-55 win on Sunday. The schools changed leads four times in the first half. But Tillman hit a jumper and a 3-pointer just after halftime to break a tie and kick off a 15-4 run that put Ohio (1-0) ahead 45-34 with 13:17 remaining. William and Mary (0-1) couldn't get closer than nine the rest of the way and shot just 36 percent in the second half compared to Ohio's 60.7 percent. Tommy Freeman scored 18 points, including four 3-pointers, Justin Orr added 16 points and Tillman grabbed 10 rebounds for the Bobcats. Danny Sumner scored 12 points, Quinn McDowell had 11 and Sean McCurdy 10 for the Tribe.
